350
00:18:50,042 --> 00:18:53,019
But she did not intend to look as if shewere interested.

351
00:18:53,019 --> 00:18:55,839
That was one of her unhappy, disagreeableways.

352
00:18:55,839 --> 00:18:59,024
So she sat still."Well," said Mrs. Medlock.

353
00:18:59,024 --> 00:19:00,062
"What do you think of it?"

354
00:19:00,062 --> 00:19:04,074
"Nothing," she answered."I know nothing about such places."

355
00:19:04,074 --> 00:19:07,037
That made Mrs. Medlock laugh a short sortof laugh.

356
00:19:07,037 --> 00:19:10,031
"Eh!" she said, "but you are like an oldwoman.

357
00:19:10,031 --> 00:19:13,083
Don't you care?""It doesn't matter" said Mary, "whether I

358
00:19:13,083 --> 00:19:14,399
care or not."

359
00:19:14,399 --> 00:19:17,029
"You are right enough there," said Mrs.Medlock.

360
00:19:17,029 --> 00:19:18,075
"It doesn't.

361
00:19:18,075 --> 00:19:22,006
What you're to be kept at MisselthwaiteManor for I don't know, unless because it's

362
00:19:22,006 --> 00:19:24,098
the easiest way.He's not going to trouble himself about

363
00:19:24,098 --> 00:19:26,048
you, that's sure and certain.

364
00:19:26,048 --> 00:19:30,005
He never troubles himself about no one."She stopped herself as if she had just

365
00:19:30,005 --> 00:19:34,036
remembered something in time."He's got a crooked back," she said.

366
00:19:34,036 --> 00:19:35,069
"That set him wrong.

367
00:19:35,069 --> 00:19:39,041
He was a sour young man and got no good ofall his money and big place till he was

368
00:19:39,041 --> 00:19:42,055
married."Mary's eyes turned toward her in spite of

369
00:19:42,055 --> 00:19:44,649
her intention not to seem to care.

370
00:19:44,649 --> 00:19:47,088
She had never thought of the hunchback'sbeing married and she was a trifle

371
00:19:47,088 --> 00:19:49,016
surprised.

372
00:19:49,016 --> 00:19:52,079
Mrs. Medlock saw this, and as she was atalkative woman she continued with more

373
00:19:52,079 --> 00:19:55,064
interest.This was one way of passing some of the

374
00:19:55,064 --> 00:19:57,035
time, at any rate.

375
00:19:57,035 --> 00:20:00,051
"She was a sweet, pretty thing and he'dhave walked the world over to get her a

376
00:20:00,051 --> 00:20:02,025
blade o' grass she wanted.

377
00:20:02,025 --> 00:20:05,076
Nobody thought she'd marry him, but shedid, and people said she married him for

378
00:20:05,076 --> 00:20:09,089
his money.But she didn't--she didn't," positively.

379
00:20:09,089 --> 00:20:10,091
