00:20:21,019 --> 00:20:25,329
It had been about a poor hunchback and abeautiful princess and it had made her

385
00:20:25,329 --> 00:20:30,002
suddenly sorry for Mr. Archibald Craven."Yes, she died," Mrs. Medlock answered.

386
00:20:30,002 --> 00:20:32,003
"And it made him queerer than ever.

387
00:20:32,003 --> 00:20:35,018
He cares about nobody.He won't see people.

388
00:20:35,018 --> 00:20:38,091
Most of the time he goes away, and when heis at Misselthwaite he shuts himself up in

389
00:20:38,091 --> 00:20:42,007
the West Wing and won't let any one butPitcher see him.

390
00:20:42,007 --> 00:20:46,042
Pitcher's an old fellow, but he took careof him when he was a child and he knows his

391
00:20:46,042 --> 00:20:48,092
ways."It sounded like something in a book and it

392
00:20:48,092 --> 00:20:50,073
did not make Mary feel cheerful.

393
00:20:50,073 --> 00:20:55,399
A house with a hundred rooms, nearly allshut up and with their doors locked--a

394
00:20:55,399 --> 00:20:59,099
house on the edge of a moor--whatsoever amoor was--sounded dreary.

395
00:20:59,099 --> 00:21:03,004
