2161
01:58:19,083 --> 01:58:24,319
saw her coming, so she always walked towardhim as silently as possible.

2162
01:58:24,319 --> 01:58:28,799
But, in fact, he did not object to her asstrongly as he had at first.

2163
01:58:28,799 --> 01:58:33,031
Perhaps he was secretly rather flattered byher evident desire for his elderly company.

2164
01:58:33,031 --> 01:58:37,002
Then, also, she was more civil than she hadbeen.

2165
01:58:37,002 --> 01:58:41,019
He did not know that when she first saw himshe spoke to him as she would have spoken

2166
01:58:41,019 --> 01:58:45,689
to a native, and had not known that across, sturdy old Yorkshire man was not

2167
01:58:45,689 --> 01:58:50,012
accustomed to salaam to his masters, and bemerely commanded by them to do things.

2168
01:58:50,012 --> 01:58:55,489
"Tha'rt like th' robin," he said to her onemorning when he lifted his head and saw her

2169
01:58:55,489 --> 01:58:56,079
standing by him.

2170
01:58:56,079 --> 01:58:59,093
