I believe I should die!"She said the last sentence quite fiercely.

2414
02:13:03,043 --> 02:13:06,092
Dickon looked more puzzled than ever andeven rubbed his hand over his rough head

2415
02:13:06,092 --> 02:13:09,063
again, but he answered quite good-humoredly.

2416
02:13:09,063 --> 02:13:12,013
"I'm keepin' secrets all th' time," hesaid.

2417
02:13:12,013 --> 02:13:16,007
"If I couldn't keep secrets from th' otherlads, secrets about foxes' cubs, an' birds'

2418
02:13:16,007 --> 02:13:21,009
nests, an' wild things' holes, there'd benaught safe on th' moor.

2419
02:13:21,009 --> 02:13:23,032
Aye, I can keep secrets."

2420
02:13:23,032 --> 02:13:27,087
Mistress Mary did not mean to put out herhand and clutch his sleeve but she did it.

2421
02:13:27,087 --> 02:13:31,061
"I've stolen a garden," she said very fast."It isn't mine.

2422
02:13:31,061 --> 02:13:32,054
It isn't anybody's.

2423
02:13:32,054 --> 02:13:36,025
Nobody wants it, nobody cares for it,nobody ever goes into it.

2424
02:13:36,025 --> 02:13:39,035
Perhaps everything is dead in it already.I don't know."

2425
02:13:39,035 --> 02:13:43,056
She began to feel hot and as contrary asshe had ever felt in her life.

2426
02:13:43,056 --> 02:13:47,021
"I don't care, I don't care!Nobody has any right to take it from me

2427
02:13:47,021 --> 02:13:49,015
when I care about it and they don't.

2428
02:13:49,015 --> 02:13:53,008
They're letting it die, all shut in byitself," she ended passionately, and she

2429
02:13:53,008 --> 02:13:58,019
threw her arms over her face and burst outcrying-poor little Mistress Mary.

2430
02:13:58,019 --> 02:14:03,003
Dickon's curious blue eyes grew rounder androunder.

2431
02:14:03,003 --> 02:14:09,001
"Eh-h-h!" he said, drawing his exclamationout slowly, and the way he did it meant

2432
02:14:09,001 --> 02:14:10,093
both wonder and sympathy.

2433
02:14:10,093 --> 02:14:15,015
"I've nothing to do," said Mary."Nothing belongs to me.

2434
02:14:15,015 --> 02:14:20,015
I found it myself and I got into it myself.I was only just like the robin, and they

2435
02:14:20,015 --> 02:14:21,054
wouldn't take it from the robin."

2436
02:14:21,054 --> 02:14:25,006
"Where is it?" asked Dickon in a droppedvoice.

2437
02:14:25,006 --> 02:14:29,007
Mistress Mary got up from the log at once.She knew she felt contrary again, and

2438
02:14:29,007 --> 02:14:32,039
obstinate, and she did not care at all.

2439
02:14:32,039 --> 02:14:36,063
She was imperious and Indian, and at thesame time hot and sorrowful.

2440
02:14:36,063 --> 02:14:41,023
"Come with me and I'll show you," she said.She led him round the laurel path and to

2441
02:14:41,023 --> 02:14:43,068
the walk where the ivy grew so thickly.

2442
02:14:43,068 --> 02:14:47,072
Dickon followed her with a queer, almostpitying, look on his face.

2443
02:14:47,072 --> 02:14:52,056
He felt as if he were being led to look atsome strange bird's nest and must move

2444
02:14:52,056 --> 02:14:54,013
softly.

2445
02:14:54,013 --> 02:14:57,088
When she stepped to the wall and lifted thehanging ivy he started.

2446
02:14:57,088 --> 02:15:03,022
There was a door and Mary pushed it slowlyopen and they passed in together, and then

2447
02:15:03,022 --> 02:15:05,078
Mary stood and waved her hand rounddefiantly.

2448
02:15:05,078 --> 02:15:07,073
"It's this," she said.

2449
02:15:07,073 --> 02:15:13,003
"It's a secret garden, and I'm the only onein the world who wants it to be alive."

2450
02:15:13,003 --> 02:15:16,098
Dickon looked round and round about it, andround and round again.

2451
02:15:16,098 --> 02:15:23,028
"Eh!" he almost whispered, "it is a queer,pretty place!

2452
02:15:23,028 --> 02:15:29,005
It's like as if a body was in a dream."

